HEADWORD: Waitress
<hw>Wait"ress</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A female waiter or
attendant; a waiting maid or waiting woman.</def> <-- esp. one employed
in a commercial dining establishment, who takes the customers' orders,
brings the meals, and otherwise serves the customers who are seated at a
table or counter. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

